What is Software ??

Article from Tech Target 
https://www.techtarget.com/searchapparchitecture/definition/software

Software is a collection of instructions, data, or programs used to operate computers and execute specific tasks. It is the intangible part of a computer system—the code that tells the hardware what to do—enabling users to interact with devices, process data, and create, edit, or consume digital content. 

Key Aspects of Software
Intangible: Unlike hardware, which is the physical, tangible component, software exists as code, programs, and procedures.
Bridge Between User and Machine: It converts human instructions into computer-actionable commands.
Functionality: Without software, hardware (computers, smartphones) would be useless. 

Main Types of Software
System Software: Manages the hardware and provides a platform for applications to run, such as operating systems (Windows, macOS, Android).
Application Software: Programs designed for end-users to perform specific tasks, such as web browsers (Chrome), word processors (Microsoft Word), or games.
Programming Software: Tools (compilers, debuggers) used by developers to create, debug, and maintain other software. 
